id: monica-api-4x-parity
title: Complete Monica 4.x API parity and resilient instance diagnostics
description: "Align monica-cli with Monica stable 4.x routes, expose missing resources and actions, and prevent systemic server failures from being misreported as endpoint incompatibility."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 0
tags[7]: agent-ux,api,diagnostics,documentation,monica-4x,read-only-safety,typescript
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:01:30.917Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T22:13:51.285Z"
deadline: "2026-07-24T19:01:30.917Z"
assignee: codex-monica-api
author: codex-monica-api
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "Every stable 4.x API route has an intentional CLI/API mapping or documented compatibility decision; Capability and research probes distinguish endpoint unsupported responses from systemic authentication/server failures; New commands provide detailed help, default TOON, valid JSON/YAML/Markdown/table output where applicable, and strict TypeScript types; All code files are at most 300 physical lines and release/coverage/read-only E2E gates pass without mutating Monica data"
definition_of_ready: "Official stable route inventory, current CLI surface, complete pm lineage, and live read-only diagnostics have been inspected."
goal: trusted-monica-cli
objective: complete-stable-api-agent-interface
value: Agents can automate the full supported Monica surface with honest machine-readable capability data.
impact: Closes silent feature gaps and prevents unsafe or impossible plans derived from false capability classifications.
outcome: Production-ready Monica 4.x route parity with read-only verified diagnostics and durable API documentation.
why_now: The requested live research exposed both missing stable routes and a production instance failure that current diagnostics misclassify.
parent: monica-platform
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 90
sprint: 2026-07-api-parity
release: 2026.7.21-2
