  monica-security-modernization,blocked_by,"2026-07-21T22:01:13.998Z",codex-monica-api,null
comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:01:30.917Z",codex-monica-api,Duplicate-safe all-status search and dedupe-audit found no existing API parity item. Monica stable 4.x source exposes statistics places lifeevents reminders/upcoming me/contact and contact work food introduction routes missing or drifted from the current reference.
  "2026-07-21T19:14:19.373Z",codex-monica-api,"User elevated repo-wide code quality to the highest priority: forbid any except documented necessity; forbid inline/dynamic imports and non-erasable TypeScript syntax; inline trivial single-use helpers; derive external types from installed declarations; enforce source LOC and high-quality docstring coverage; require honest 100/100/100/100 source coverage with efficient non-duplicative tests across unit, integration, functional, smoke, read-only E2E/dogfood, performance, acceptance and PM validation; strengthen mandatory CI quality/security/duplication gates without exclusion-based or synthetic coverage cheating."
  "2026-07-21T19:31:45.010Z",codex-monica-api,"Re-verified the authoritative Monica 4.x source live on 2026-07-21: head remains 32028ce3ce79cef38df5d27a297e5b20680f0065. routes/api.php plus Place, LifeEvent, Reminder, Avatar, Me controllers/services/resources confirm statistics, places, lifeevents, reminders/upcoming/{month}, POST/DELETE me/contact, PUT contact work/food/introduction/avatar and their request/response fields."
  "2026-07-21T20:03:51.575Z",codex-monica-api,"Refactored duplicated legacy command handlers for activities, gifts, journal, and reminders onto the typed CRUD execution kernel. Added strict union/integer parsers, exact option-to-API mappings, custom upcoming/photo actions, and focused coverage. Full suite remains green; coverage remediation continues without threshold exclusions or ignore directives."
  "2026-07-21T21:47:17.504Z",codex-monica-api,"Implemented the stable Monica 4.x parity surface: places and life-events CRUD, public statistics, upcoming reminders, me/contact association, introduction/avatar/work/food profile actions, typed CRUD/attachment kernels, complete help registration, and source-derived API snapshots. Refactored adjacent legacy handlers onto typed shared execution without changing live data."
  "2026-07-21T22:01:19.225Z",codex-monica-api,"Read-only acceptance is green: 95 actual monica command checks, 42 locally verifiable passes, 53 expected API-dependent failures after an independent unhealthy capability preflight, zero unexplained failures, five mutation guards blocked locally, and private settings restored. The server remains unavailable because Laravel cannot write storage logs; no Monica data was changed."
  "2026-07-21T22:06:22.969Z",codex-monica-api,"Version policy selected 2026.7.21-2 because one release tag already exists for 2026-07-21; package, lockfile, and PM release metadata are aligned."
  "2026-07-21T22:13:51.284Z",codex-monica-api,"PR #59 CI round 1 found two actionable portability/security issues: GitHub runners lacked rg for the source-quality script, and CodeQL flagged the unbounded email regex. Replaced discovery with Node filesystem traversal and email validation with linear bounded string checks; added eight malformed-email cases. Local proof is 838 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 and zero dependency vulnerabilities."
notes[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:01:30.917Z",codex-monica-api,The supplied instance currently fails every API request with HTTP 500 because Laravel cannot append storage/logs/laravel-2026-07-21.log and also reports Cloudflare trust-proxy loading failure. Treat this as systemic instance health not 31 unsupported resources; do not store credentials in pm.
  "2026-07-21T19:14:49.780Z",codex-monica-api,"Decision: coverage, docstrings, LOC, strict TypeScript syntax, duplication, PM lint, and reproducible security/quality checks are release-blocking gates. Existing violations are in scope repo-wide, including pre-existing oversized source and test files."
  "2026-07-21T19:31:45.949Z",codex-monica-api,"Honest all-source Vitest coverage now blocks release at 52.77% statements, 53.89% branches, 68.43% functions, 52.77% lines with 553 passing tests. Thresholds remain 100/100/100/100; no source exclusions or synthetic coverage bypasses will be used."
  "2026-07-21T21:47:18.073Z",codex-monica-api,"Verification milestone: 113 Vitest files and 830 tests pass with exact 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, and 100% lines across every src TypeScript file. Repo-wide quality gate covers 247 source/test files, 574/574 documented exports, <=300 executable lines, no explicit any, no inline/dynamic imports, and erasable TypeScript only. jscpd duplication is 4.53% under the 5% gate."
  "2026-07-21T22:01:20.394Z",codex-monica-api,"Security decision: pin fixed transitive brace-expansion, flatted, js-yaml, and picomatch releases through Bun overrides because current tool dependency ranges retained nine known DoS/prototype-pollution advisories. bun audit now reports zero vulnerabilities and the exact repository gate remains green."
learnings[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:01:30.917Z",codex-monica-api,Documentation-only endpoint coverage can report 100 percent while source-route parity is incomplete; route-source provenance and systemic-failure semantics must be first-class research data.
  "2026-07-21T19:31:46.832Z",codex-monica-api,"The CLI had broad endpoint wrapper tests but most Commander action bodies and the real HTTP/config runtime were not executed, so previous narrow coverage floors concealed command-layer and client-layer risk."
  "2026-07-21T21:47:18.663Z",codex-monica-api,"A live E2E harness must distinguish product failures from an unavailable self-hosted instance without hiding either: the configured server returns a Laravel storage/logs permission failure, while write-guard commands prove every attempted mutation is blocked locally before fetch. The report records unavailable commands as expected infrastructure failures and preserves/restores private settings byte-for-byte."
  "2026-07-21T22:01:21.602Z",codex-monica-api,"Exact-head bot review governance benefits from a single GraphQL inventory that includes conversation comments, submitted reviews, inline threads, resolution state, reactions, and check runs; native reaction/reply/resolve operations make acknowledgement auditable instead of relying on a flat PR summary."
